I was really surprised to find a good diner in the heart of south Brooklyn. Despite all the good reviews, I just didn't think a breakfast place would live up to NJ/LI diners. However, the atmosphere is nice, the service was fast, and most importantly - the veggie omelet and french toast were delicious! Is this an exquisite, fancy breakfast place? No.  Is it dependable, hearty breakfast serving diner staples? Absolutely. Can't wait to come back!
